[Course_Description]
Explore techniques and exercises that can help you grow as a vocalist. In this course—the second in a series focusing on learning how to sing—learn concepts that can provide you with a solid foundation as a singer. Professional vocalist Lari White explains how musical relationships work in chords, scales, and intervals. She also helps you train your ear to identify common sounds, and provides some foundational warm-up exercises for both your voice and body. To wrap up, Lari helps you shape your vocal sound by helping you understand pitch and tone and how they work within your vocal range and register. Note: This course was recorded and produced by ArtistWorks. We're pleased to host this training in our library.